  DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN

    The xxddiittvviieeww(1X11R5) program displays ddiittrrooffff output on an X display. It
    uses no special metrics and automatically converts the printer coordinates
    into screen coordinates. It uses the user-specified screen resolution
    rather than the actual resolution so that the appropriate fonts can be
    found. If -- is given as the filename, xxddiittvviieeww(1X11R5) reads from standard
    input. If "|" is the first character of filename, xxddiittvviieeww(1X11R5) forks
    sshh(1) to run the rest of the "file name" and uses the standard output of
    that command.

